                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.612 Grapes/24/Spain: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moore</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-04-03T11:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 3, 1924—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 3—10:03 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>15. Had long serious interview with Spanish Foreign Minister and chief of treaty
                    commission, who stated that so long as importation of Spanish grapes is
                    peremptorily prohibited by United States, Spanish Government positively has no
                    interest in negotiating new treaty or proroguing old one. Spanish Government
                    asserts that activities of California grape growers is cause of action Spanish
                    grapes.</p>
                <p>Please telegraph instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
